00:04:17.108 --> 00:04:19.038
And I will teach you that in this video.

00:04:19.063 --> 00:04:22.256
How do the hidden terms and conditions of better policies appear like?

00:04:22.256 --> 00:04:25.600
How do hidden terms &amp; conditions of bad or slightly bad policies appear like?

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:28.333
You evaluate your current policy after understanding that.

00:04:28.333 --> 00:04:30.000
If you think this is a wrong policy,

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:33.760
then you must definitely port the policy into a good policy.

00:04:33.785 --> 00:04:35.415
The benefit of porting would be...

00:04:35.415 --> 00:04:39.797
you won't have to endure the waiting periods that you've already been through.

00:04:39.822 --> 00:04:42.863
But if you've increased the sum insured during the porting time.

00:04:42.863 --> 00:04:45.940
then additional waiting period will be levied on the additional sum insured.

00:04:45.940 --> 00:04:49.440
The continued sum insured will remain untouched.

00:04:49.440 --> 00:04:51.266
HOW TO FIND BAD POLICIES

00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:55.462
After shortlisting the company, we must also know how to shortlist a good plan.

00:04:55.487 --> 00:04:57.241
There is an elimination technique for that too.

00:04:57.266 --> 00:05:00.154
You have to avoid policies with three evil features.

00:05:00.179 --> 00:05:03.440
Room rent limit, disease-wise sublimit, and Copay.

00:05:03.440 --> 00:05:07.230
In most policies, you'll get a room rent limit, such as 1% of the sum insured.

00:05:07.255 --> 00:05:10.280
Or else the room type will be written as 'Single AC private room'.

00:05:10.280 --> 00:05:14.291
This means If you get treated by opting for a larger or a higher priced room.

00:05:14.316 --> 00:05:16.668
For example, your base sum assured is Rs 10 lakhs.

00:05:16.668 --> 00:05:18.840
And you are only allowed a single AC private room...

00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:22.782
 which is the cheapest room in a hospital and it's price is Rs 3,000.

00:05:22.807 --> 00:05:25.334
But, you opted for a Rs 5000 per night room.

00:05:25.359 --> 00:05:26.811
And you were admitted for five days.

00:05:26.836 --> 00:05:28.995
then your room rent costed Rs 25,000.

00:05:28.995 --> 00:05:32.698
The total eligible surgery expense was Rs 5 lakhs.

00:05:32.723 --> 00:05:35.081
then your total bill was Rs 5,25,000.

00:05:35.106 --> 00:05:38.671
Now you assumed that instead of Rs 3,000; I opted for Rs 5000 room.

00:05:38.696 --> 00:05:41.075
I spent an additional of Rs 2000 every day.

00:05:41.100 --> 00:05:42.399
And you were admitted for five days.

00:05:42.399 --> 00:05:45.392
That means you have to pay Rs 10,000 from your own pocket.

00:05:45.417 --> 00:05:50.280
And you will get the remaining Rs 5,15,000 expense in the form of a claim from policy.

00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:52.060
Eventually, the insurance company will tell you...

00:05:52.085 --> 00:05:57.118
The room rent limit in your policy is only 60% of your actual room rent.

00:05:57.143 --> 00:06:00.724
You will only get 60% on your claim of Rs 5 lakhs.

00:06:00.749 --> 00:06:03.560
i.e. Rs 3,00,000. You will have to pay Rs 2,00,000 from your pocket.

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:05.707
And there is no use of such a policy.

00:06:05.732 --> 00:06:08.458
Disease wise sublimit is also a very big scam.

00:06:08.458 --> 00:06:11.622
Maybe the company will tell you that you've a sum insured of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:06:11.622 --> 00:06:16.422
But you won't find a treatment for you to claim Rs 50 lakhs on, because...

00:06:16.422 --> 00:06:18.366
The treatment of every type is predefined...

00:06:18.391 --> 00:06:21.935
and there is a maximum limit defined on how much you can claim on it.

00:06:21.960 --> 00:06:23.788
And the worst thing I find is...

00:06:23.788 --> 00:06:26.649
It could be possible in today's times for several diseases that...

00:06:26.649 --> 00:06:30.697
cutting-edge, technologically advanced treatments are available in good hospitals.

00:06:30.722 --> 00:06:32.205
But I won't be able to do that.

00:06:32.230 --> 00:06:34.840
So there must not be a disease wise sub-limit.

00:06:34.840 --> 00:06:36.290
3. Copay.

00:06:36.315 --> 00:06:39.720
This means the admissible claim amount, not the total claim.

00:06:39.720 --> 00:06:41.760
which the company considers as worth paying...

00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:46.032
A certain percentage of it, i.e. 20% or 30%, you pay from your pocket.

00:06:46.057 --> 00:06:47.553
I will share one real example...

00:06:47.553 --> 00:06:49.831
If you have all three features mentioned in the policy,

00:06:49.856 --> 00:06:52.284
then how your Rs 15 lakhs policy is useless?

00:06:52.309 --> 00:06:55.447
Sum insured is Rs 15 lakhs. You claimed Rs 10 lakhs.

00:06:55.472 --> 00:06:59.483
And firstly we will consider the admissible claim amount, which comes to Rs 8 lakhs.

00:06:59.508 --> 00:07:00.721
Where are the 2 lakh rupees?

00:07:00.746 --> 00:07:03.663
2 lakhs have been deducted from the expensive room you opted for.

00:07:03.663 --> 00:07:07.301
The admissible claim amount is Rs 8 lakhs, but you've to give 20%.

00:07:07.301 --> 00:07:10.334
i.e. it's confirmed that you have to pay Rs 2,40,000.

00:07:10.334 --> 00:07:11.614
But what do you get to know after that?

00:07:11.639 --> 00:07:13.903
There is a 5 lakh sub limit on disease.

00:07:13.903 --> 00:07:14.696
What's happening is.

00:07:14.696 --> 00:07:17.988
Admissible claim amount and sub limit, whichever is lower, is been checked.

00:07:18.013 --> 00:07:20.118
The company is holding onto the lower amount and stating...

00:07:20.118 --> 00:07:21.362
we will only provide the lower amount.

00:07:21.387 --> 00:07:24.592
So half of the amount from the claim of Rs 10 lakhs, or sometimes more...

00:07:24.592 --> 00:07:26.204
needs to be paid from your end.

00:07:26.204 --> 00:07:30.640
If you've room rent, disease-wise sub limit and copay, all in one policy.

