00:10:36.560 --> 00:10:39.080
TYPES OF WAITING PERIODS

00:10:39.080 --> 00:10:41.934
There is a standard waiting period, which you must be aware of.

00:10:41.934 --> 00:10:44.702
You cannot claim within 30 days of purchasing the policy,

00:10:44.727 --> 00:10:45.935
expect for accidents.

00:10:45.960 --> 00:10:48.711
After that comes the waiting period of pre existing disease,

00:10:48.711 --> 00:10:49.897
which usually is for 3 years.

00:10:49.922 --> 00:10:52.215
But you can reduce this by adding a rider.

00:10:52.215 --> 00:10:54.934
How can you do it? On which policy? We will see that.

00:10:54.959 --> 00:10:57.357
But you will have to disclose the pre existing diseases.

00:10:57.382 --> 00:10:58.811
Or else you will face a major issue.

00:10:58.836 --> 00:11:00.559
The claim might get rejected in the future.

00:11:00.559 --> 00:11:04.045
And you will have to by default survive the waiting period of three years.

00:11:04.070 --> 00:11:07.902
The next thing you need to remember is the specific diseases waiting period.

00:11:07.902 --> 00:11:09.375
Or else slow growing diseases.

00:11:09.400 --> 00:11:13.712
Such as kidney stones, cataract, anal fissure, etc.

00:11:13.737 --> 00:11:16.286
The list is on the screen, you can refer to the type of diseases mentioned.

00:11:16.311 --> 00:11:18.401
If you don't have diseases while purchasing the policy,

00:11:18.426 --> 00:11:21.482
then you won't get the cover for the first two years.

00:11:21.507 --> 00:11:24.160
This is a waiting period, which you have to survive.

00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:26.013
PRE AND POST HOSPITALIZATION

00:11:26.013 --> 00:11:30.348
You will get pre and post hospitalization cover in almost all the policies.

00:11:30.373 --> 00:11:33.895
It means that before the main treatment or surgery,

00:11:33.895 --> 00:11:37.490
i.e. your expenses of 60 or 90 days get covered.

00:11:37.490 --> 00:11:40.345
And after surgery, i.e. post-hospitalisation expenses...

00:11:40.345 --> 00:11:42.964
are covered up to 180 days in certain policies.

00:11:42.989 --> 00:11:43.894
Which expenses?

00:11:43.919 --> 00:11:46.216
All the expenses that are related to your main treatment.

00:11:46.216 --> 00:11:48.312
It means If you had done 10-12 tests.

00:11:48.337 --> 00:11:52.219
You got it done because you had to undergo surgery based on the results.

00:11:52.244 --> 00:11:54.031
You will get the test expense reimbursed.

00:11:54.056 --> 00:11:57.671
After surgery, If the doctor has prescribed that you need to take physiotherapy,

00:11:57.696 --> 00:12:01.523
or more medications, related to the surgery, for recovery.

00:12:01.548 --> 00:12:03.332
That expense will also be covered.

00:12:03.357 --> 00:12:06.722
The catch is most people aren't aware of such a feature in their policy,

00:12:06.722 --> 00:12:07.640
hence they don't claim it.

00:12:07.640 --> 00:12:13.080
You need to keep all the bills carefully and submit after 180 days.

00:12:13.080 --> 00:12:15.736
NO CLAIM BONUS

00:12:15.761 --> 00:12:17.493
It's self-explanatory, 'No Claim Bonus'.

00:12:17.493 --> 00:12:19.151
It means If you don't claim it this year,

00:12:19.176 --> 00:12:22.978
then you will get a little cover in the additional no claims bucket.

00:12:23.003 --> 00:12:25.402
The cover will vary from policy to policy.

00:12:25.427 --> 00:12:28.336
Certain policies offer 20%, certain offer 50%, every year.

00:12:28.336 --> 00:12:32.017
Certain companies have changed the name of 'No claim bonus' to 'Bonus'.

00:12:32.017 --> 00:12:34.505
It means they have given fancy names from policy to policy.

00:12:34.530 --> 00:12:37.438
And now companies are stating whether you claim it or not.

00:12:37.463 --> 00:12:41.940
We will keep giving you bonus of 20% - 50% every year, please don't deny it.

00:12:45.611 --> 00:12:49.562
And even If you claim the no claim bonus or bonus won't be deleted.

00:12:49.587 --> 00:12:52.040
There will still be some conditions, which you'll have to read...

00:12:52.065 --> 00:12:53.559
and I'll tell you where it's written.

00:12:53.584 --> 00:12:54.902
RESTORATION BENEFITS

00:12:54.927 --> 00:12:56.657
The next benefit is restoration.

00:12:56.657 --> 00:13:00.262
It's every company's favourite feature and is promoted a lot.

00:13:00.287 --> 00:13:03.000
They like to say that when your sum insured ends,

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:06.528
your base sum insured will be restored again.

00:13:06.553 --> 00:13:09.388
It's quite useful in the family floater policy.

00:13:09.413 --> 00:13:12.869
Assume that it's a 4-member family and the policy is for Rs 20 lakhs.

00:13:12.894 --> 00:13:15.696
So it's not like the 20 lakh cover will be given to each individual.

00:13:15.721 --> 00:13:19.431
It's a 20 lakh shared cover, which will be beneficial for everyone.

00:13:19.431 --> 00:13:23.513
And If within a year, one family member has to undergo an expensive treatment.

00:13:23.538 --> 00:13:25.653
And the Rs 20 lakhs are used up for it.

00:13:25.653 --> 00:13:28.788
Then, no cover will be left for the remaining three members for that year.

00:13:28.813 --> 00:13:31.234
And If in that case, the cover is restored.

00:13:31.259 --> 00:13:32.849
It will be beneficial for the other members too.

00:13:32.874 --> 00:13:36.520
Some companies will restore your base sum assured only once per year.

00:13:36.545 --> 00:13:39.200
And some will restore unlimited times in a year.

00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:40.900
Here is where the gimmick starts.

00:13:40.925 --> 00:13:42.596
If you are restoring it unlimited times,

00:13:42.596 --> 00:13:44.510
then there is no issue at all.

00:13:44.510 --> 00:13:46.507
I will opt for a 5 - 10 lakh basic policy.

00:13:46.532 --> 00:13:49.381
When the 5 - 10 lakhs is used up, I will restore it again.

00:13:49.406 --> 00:13:50.368
What's the tension?

00:13:50.393 --> 00:13:55.066
There is tension, but for that you need to know about 'Claim Utilization Sequence'.

00:13:55.091 --> 00:13:57.647
You will get this in the policy wording of every company.

00:13:57.647 --> 00:14:01.122
Every company has a sequence and mostly the sequence is similar.

00:14:01.147 --> 00:14:02.568
1. Base Sum Assured.

00:14:02.593 --> 00:14:04.029
2. No claim bonus.

00:14:04.054 --> 00:14:06.763
3. After that additional cover or rider which you've opted for.

00:14:06.788 --> 00:14:08.600
4. And restoration comes towards the end.

00:14:08.600 --> 00:14:10.553
Now depending on how easily...

00:14:10.553 --> 00:14:13.440
the company wants you to have restoration benefit.

00:14:13.440 --> 00:14:16.520
The terms and conditions are drafted accordingly.

00:14:16.520 --> 00:14:20.735
First example, Policy A - We are claiming it for the first time.

00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:22.692
The base sum assured is of Rs 10 lakhs.

00:14:22.692 --> 00:14:25.004
We have received the no claim bonus of Rs 5 lakhs.

00:14:25.044 --> 00:14:27.982
If we have opted for an additional cover, then it's for Rs 10 Crores.

00:14:28.007 --> 00:14:29.413
Let's assume we have it.

00:14:29.438 --> 00:14:31.231
And finally the restoration would be Rs 10 lakhs.

00:14:31.256 --> 00:14:34.889
Which is equal to the base sum insured, that benefit is on paper now.

00:14:34.889 --> 00:14:36.889
We claimed for Rs 20 lakhs.

00:14:36.889 --> 00:14:40.190
Firstly, Rs 10 lakhs will be deducted from your base sum insured,

00:14:40.215 --> 00:14:41.870
and that will be entirely emptied.

00:14:41.870 --> 00:14:44.172
After that the no claim bonus is of Rs 5 lakhs.

00:14:44.172 --> 00:14:48.011
So the next Rs 5 lakh will be taken from 'No Claim Bonus'. It will be used up too.

00:14:48.036 --> 00:14:50.629
After that you had an additional cover of Rs 10 lakhs.

00:14:50.629 --> 00:14:53.007
Rs 5 lakh would be claimed from that.

00:14:53.032 --> 00:14:56.520
And Rs 5 lakh additional cover would still remain.

00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:59.332
Now, in the same year, we will claim Rs 10 lakhs for the second time.

00:14:59.357 --> 00:15:01.037
The base sum assured is zero.

00:15:01.037 --> 00:15:02.874
The no-claim bonus is zero.

00:15:02.899 --> 00:15:04.822
Rs 5 lakh is remaining in the additional cover.

00:15:04.822 --> 00:15:07.482
Your claim will be settled for Rs 5 lakhs.

00:15:07.507 --> 00:15:11.440
And you will have to pay the remaining Rs 5 lakhs from your pocket.

00:15:11.440 --> 00:15:13.090
Now you will ask where is the restoration?

00:15:13.115 --> 00:15:14.981
Restoration remained on paper itself.

00:15:15.006 --> 00:15:17.890
Because it's written in the terms and conditions of the policy,

00:15:17.915 --> 00:15:20.518
In one single hospitalization of yours,

00:15:20.518 --> 00:15:24.228
Base Sum Assured, No Claim Bonus, Additional Cover (if any).

00:15:24.253 --> 00:15:26.500
The calculation after adding everything must be zero.

00:15:26.525 --> 00:15:29.829
Your base sum assured will be restored only after that.

00:15:29.854 --> 00:15:31.318
Because while claiming for the second time,

00:15:31.318 --> 00:15:33.706
you had Rs 5 lakhs in your additional cover.

00:15:33.706 --> 00:15:35.539
So the base sum assured won't be restored.

00:15:35.564 --> 00:15:38.223
And you will have to pay the remaining Rs 5 lakhs from your pocket.

00:15:38.223 --> 00:15:39.792
Now when you claim for the third time,

00:15:39.792 --> 00:15:43.288
your base sum assured of Rs 10 lakhs will certainly be restored.

00:15:43.313 --> 00:15:47.181
But the thing is, whether you get hospitalized for the third time,

00:15:47.206 --> 00:15:50.000
or whether the year gets completed and the policy renews next year.

00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:54.440
Anyways your base sum assured, no claim bonus, additional cover will be restored.

00:15:54.440 --> 00:15:56.914
That means your fault or your hospital's fault would be...

00:15:56.914 --> 00:15:59.000
Why was your hospital bill invoiced Rs 5 lakhs lesser?

00:16:00.658 --> 00:16:02.659
The first claim must have been of Rs 20 lakhs.

00:16:02.687 --> 00:16:03.907
Make it zero there itself.

00:16:03.932 --> 00:16:06.910
So that you get the restoration benefit in the next claim.

00:16:06.935 --> 00:16:09.560
You will find a different type of restoration in several policies.

00:16:09.560 --> 00:16:11.129
Let's consider Policy B's example.

00:16:11.154 --> 00:16:13.775
We have a base sum insured in this too.

00:16:13.775 --> 00:16:16.464
No claim bonus of Rs 5 lakhs, additional cover of Rs 10 lakhs.

00:16:16.464 --> 00:16:20.000
The restoration benefit which is available of Rs 10 lakhs, still on paper...

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:21.637
and your claim is of Rs 20 lakhs.

00:16:21.662 --> 00:16:23.877
So, Rs 10 lakhs will be deducted based on base sum insured.

00:16:23.902 --> 00:16:25.757
Rs 5 lakhs on no claim bonus.

00:16:25.757 --> 00:16:28.661
And Rs 5 lakhs will be deducted on additional cover as well.

00:16:28.686 --> 00:16:30.823
And now you have an additional cover remaining of Rs 5 lakhs.

00:16:30.848 --> 00:16:34.206
But it's written in the terms and conditions of this policy that..

00:16:34.231 --> 00:16:36.647
If your base sum insured in the first claim...

00:16:36.672 --> 00:16:39.496
It's either fully or gets partially utilized,

00:16:39.521 --> 00:16:42.556
then you can restore it in another claim.

00:16:42.581 --> 00:16:46.944
Regardless of any cover available on no claim bonus or additional rider.

00:16:46.969 --> 00:16:49.549
Here when you claim for Rs 10 lakhs for the second time.

00:16:49.574 --> 00:16:52.377
Rs 5 lakhs will be deducted from your additional cover.

00:16:52.402 --> 00:16:55.761
The remaining Rs 5 lakhs will be deducted from your restoration.

00:16:55.786 --> 00:16:59.234
The restoration benefit will be maximum as per your base sum assured.

00:16:59.259 --> 00:17:02.524
Here in your base sum assured, your requirement was only of Rs 5 lakhs.

00:17:02.549 --> 00:17:04.343
It will be restored by Rs 5 lakhs.

00:17:04.368 --> 00:17:05.875
Now this is very practical.

00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:09.341
You will get a chance to claim restoration during the second hospitalization.

00:17:09.341 --> 00:17:12.177
And you won't have to pay those Rs 5 lakhs from your own pocket.

00:17:12.202 --> 00:17:16.465
Moral of the story: You will get unlimited restoration option in certain policies.

00:17:16.490 --> 00:17:18.889
You need to check the conditions of it.

00:17:18.914 --> 00:17:21.947
Will they help you utilize it or is just on paper?

00:17:21.972 --> 00:17:23.973
Some more hidden terms of restoration.

00:17:23.998 --> 00:17:28.074
In certain policies, you will find unlimited restoration, but there will be a catch...

00:17:28.074 --> 00:17:31.151
They will do unlimited times for unrelated illnesses.

00:17:31.151 --> 00:17:32.548
Won't do it for related illness.

00:17:32.548 --> 00:17:36.357
Related illness means you get hospitalized owing to a heart condition.

00:17:36.382 --> 00:17:39.871
And you are getting hospitalized again due to the heart condition.

00:17:39.896 --> 00:17:41.433
That's a related illness.

00:17:41.458 --> 00:17:43.920
Maybe you won't get the benefit of restoration.

00:17:43.920 --> 00:17:46.006
If you are going for a knee operation, then you might get it.

00:17:46.031 --> 00:17:47.960
In certain policies, there is an additional condition,

00:17:47.985 --> 00:17:50.080
You will get it for a related illness.

00:17:50.105 --> 00:17:53.894
But there must be a 45-day gap after your next hospitalisation.

00:17:53.919 --> 00:17:55.687
We can try to manage it somehow.

00:17:55.687 --> 00:17:57.464
But it's well and good If this condition didn't exist.

00:17:57.489 --> 00:17:59.798
COMPARING MULTIPLE POLICIES IN
 ONE PLACE

00:17:59.798 --> 00:18:04.770
Now we will compare HDFC Ergo Optima Secure &amp; ICICI Lombard Elevate plan.

00:18:04.795 --> 00:18:06.082
Now these two companies, because...

00:18:06.082 --> 00:18:08.804
their incurred claims ratio and complaints data is good.

00:18:08.829 --> 00:18:10.093
And these two plans because...

00:18:10.118 --> 00:18:12.769
Both of these are flagship plans of the respective companies.

00:18:12.794 --> 00:18:14.512
Firstly, we will start the feature wise comparison.

00:18:14.537 --> 00:18:16.774
I will take you further in depth.

00:18:16.799 --> 00:18:20.000
I will open the policy documents of both policies side by side.

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:22.685
I will teach you how to find the hidden terms and conditions.

00:18:22.710 --> 00:18:27.305
By learning this exercise, you can analyse your existing policy and derive that...

00:18:27.330 --> 00:18:31.720
Can you claim the fancy features of your policy?

00:18:31.720 --> 00:18:33.974
So the HDFCs Optima Secure plan...

00:18:33.999 --> 00:18:36.087
And I will compare ICICI's Elevate.

00:18:36.112 --> 00:18:38.766
Firstly, you will notice that HDFC's premium is more.

00:18:38.766 --> 00:18:40.019
Rs 22,308.

00:18:40.044 --> 00:18:43.560
Whereas, ICICI Elevate's premium is Rs 14,285.

00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:46.772
This premium is for a 30 year old man who is fit and fine.

00:18:46.797 --> 00:18:50.300
That is because you get a base sum insured of Rs 50 lakhs in ICICI.

00:18:50.300 --> 00:18:53.473
Whereas in HDFC, along with a base sum insured of Rs 50 lakhs...

00:18:53.498 --> 00:18:56.445
You get an extra of Rs 50 lakhs from Day 1.

00:18:56.470 --> 00:18:59.282
This is called HDFC Ergo's Secure Benefit.

00:18:59.317 --> 00:19:02.936
After that you will notice, there is no limit on HDFC's room rent limit.

00:19:02.961 --> 00:19:06.169
But there is a single private AC room limit in ICICI.

00:19:06.194 --> 00:19:11.182
If you look at the policy wordings, then it's written that the cheapest room is allowed.

00:19:11.207 --> 00:19:15.328
If you even go one step above, then you will have a proportionate deduction.

00:19:15.353 --> 00:19:18.237
Now you might be wondering how can it happen in the flagship plan?

00:19:18.262 --> 00:19:20.193
It's because the elevate plan is quite cheap.

00:19:20.193 --> 00:19:24.116
And it's cheap because instead of including it's important features here...

00:19:24.141 --> 00:19:25.664
It is sold with additional riders.

00:19:25.689 --> 00:19:29.578
Then it's something to talk about that If you add useful riders in this.

00:19:29.603 --> 00:19:31.413
To make this a useable policy.

00:19:31.438 --> 00:19:34.373
So will it's premium come close to Optima Secure?

00:19:34.373 --> 00:19:38.513
In it's detailed comparison, you can compare rest of the features easily.

00:19:38.538 --> 00:19:40.335
This will give you an overview.

00:19:40.360 --> 00:19:42.398
Which policy has which types of features?

00:19:42.398 --> 00:19:44.398
But how useful are those features?

00:19:44.398 --> 00:19:48.665
To understand that, let us understand the police wordings of both the policies.

00:19:48.690 --> 00:19:51.256
You will get the policy wordings on Policy Bazaar itself.

00:19:51.281 --> 00:19:54.329
Wherein you are watching all the premium and riders calculation.

00:19:54.354 --> 00:19:57.527
And If you click on 'All Features' and then scroll down,

00:19:57.527 --> 00:20:01.280
then that policy's 'policy wording document' is available for download.

00:20:01.280 --> 00:20:03.745
UNDERSTANDING HIDDEN TERMS AND CONDITIONS

00:20:03.745 --> 00:20:05.659
Firstly, sum assured, as I mentioned before...

00:20:05.659 --> 00:20:10.339
In HDFC, with the base sum assured, you get the same amount in secure benefit.

00:20:10.364 --> 00:20:12.215
which is applicable from Day 1.

00:20:12.215 --> 00:20:15.001
And you can claim it from first hospitalization itself.

00:20:15.026 --> 00:20:17.206
Is there any hidden condition in it, let's find out.

00:20:20.195 --> 00:20:21.614
This is the secure benefit.

00:20:21.639 --> 00:20:24.652
It's written here, 'the additional amount as specified in the policy schedule...

00:20:24.652 --> 00:20:27.126
will be available to the insured person as sum insured...

00:20:27.126 --> 00:20:31.472
for all claims admissable under Section B and Section B.2.3

00:20:31.497 --> 00:20:33.195
which is called 'Protect Benefit'.

00:20:33.195 --> 00:20:37.153
All the coverage is written in Section B.

00:20:37.178 --> 00:20:41.159
And the section B.2.3 protect benefit is the consumables cover.

00:20:41.159 --> 00:20:44.495
Yes, you also get consumables cover in Optima Secure.

00:20:44.495 --> 00:20:46.720
And it's a good thing, that it's written in secure benefit...

00:20:46.745 --> 00:20:49.364
you can avail secure benefit in both types of covers.

00:20:49.389 --> 00:20:53.377
Any unutilized amount, in whole or in part will not be carried forward...

00:20:53.402 --> 00:20:55.035
to the subsequent policy year.

00:20:55.060 --> 00:20:55.744
It states that,

00:20:55.744 --> 00:21:00.892
you will keep getting a similar additional amount of base sum insured every year.

00:21:00.917 --> 00:21:02.711
But you can't add that each year.

00:21:02.736 --> 00:21:03.841
It's also written in the next point that,

00:21:03.866 --> 00:21:08.536
you can use secure benefit for one claim or multiple claims in a year.

00:21:08.561 --> 00:21:10.504
So If it's a 50 lakh policy.

00:21:10.529 --> 00:21:12.721
So it's technically a Rs 1 Crore policy.

00:21:12.746 --> 00:21:14.032
I can use it anyhow.

00:21:14.057 --> 00:21:17.265
There is no secure benefit in ICICI Elevate.

00:21:17.290 --> 00:21:18.985
Now we will compare no claim bonus,

00:21:18.985 --> 00:21:21.700
which is termed as 'Plus benefit' in HDFC.

00:21:22.855 --> 00:21:24.013
It's written in Point A that,

00:21:24.038 --> 00:21:28.279
you can accumulate this as 100% base sum assured.

00:21:28.304 --> 00:21:31.747
It's written in Policy B that you will be given this after completing a year.

00:21:31.772 --> 00:21:34.562
You can carry it forward which I've told you.

00:21:34.562 --> 00:21:36.634
There must not be a break in your policy.

00:21:36.659 --> 00:21:40.795
In Point C, it's written, whether you claim it or not, you will get the plus benefit.

00:21:40.820 --> 00:21:41.614
It's a great thing.

00:21:41.639 --> 00:21:44.186
It means Optima Secure is such a policy,

00:21:44.211 --> 00:21:46.373
whose cover is doubled from day one.

00:21:46.398 --> 00:21:48.200
i.e. you are getting the secure benefit.

00:21:48.200 --> 00:21:51.406
The cover is 2.5x in the initial part of second year.

00:21:51.406 --> 00:21:53.707
You might have got a plus benefit of 50%.

00:21:53.755 --> 00:21:55.320
And in the start of third year,

00:21:55.320 --> 00:21:59.590
your total cover has now become 3x, i.e. your cover will become 1.5 crores.

00:21:59.615 --> 00:22:01.560
If you opt for a 50 lakh policy.

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:04.971
After this, the scenarios have been further explained in notes.

00:22:04.996 --> 00:22:07.759
For example, read point 5 and 6.

00:22:07.784 --> 00:22:12.412
It's written that If you deduct the cover during the policy renewal next year.

00:22:12.437 --> 00:22:14.287
You reduced it from 50 lakhs to 25 lakhs.

00:22:14.312 --> 00:22:16.974
You will get the plus benefit for Rs 25 lakhs.

00:22:16.974 --> 00:22:21.220
But in point 6, it's written If you increase the cover during renewal next year.

00:22:21.245 --> 00:22:22.991
You increased it from Rs 50 lakhs to 1 Crore.

00:22:23.016 --> 00:22:25.774
You won't get the plus benefit on Rs 1 crore but on Rs 50 lakhs.

00:22:25.774 --> 00:22:27.315
And the last point is also important for you.

00:22:27.340 --> 00:22:30.294
New insured person added to the policy during subsequent renewal...

00:22:30.319 --> 00:22:33.583
will be eligible for the plus benefit as per the renewal terms.

00:22:33.608 --> 00:22:36.363
Now it's written as per their renewal terms.

00:22:36.388 --> 00:22:39.192
If the new person's renewal terms are different.

00:22:39.217 --> 00:22:43.370
It means they will get base sum assured, secured benefit,

00:22:43.395 --> 00:22:45.462
But they won't get plus benefit from Day 1.

00:22:45.462 --> 00:22:47.462
They will also have to go through a year.

00:22:47.462 --> 00:22:50.116
They will get 50% + benefit on the next renewal.

00:22:50.141 --> 00:22:54.138
And on the next renewal after that, they will get 50% plus benefit.

00:22:54.163 --> 00:22:57.428
Now this plus benefit, which is the new term for no claim bonus.

00:22:57.453 --> 00:23:00.000
Let's search that in ICICI Elevate.

00:23:00.806 --> 00:23:03.809
They have stated their annual renewal bonus as...

00:23:04.188 --> 00:23:05.315
Loyalty Bonus.

00:23:05.340 --> 00:23:08.326
It's written here that they will provide a 20% loyalty bonus.

00:23:08.326 --> 00:23:10.240
Every year. Irrespective of our claim.

00:23:10.240 --> 00:23:12.987
That means even If you claim or don't, you will still get it.

00:23:13.012 --> 00:23:16.436
 Provided that the policy has been continuously renewed with the company...

00:23:16.436 --> 00:23:19.557
It means that there should not be a break between your policy.

00:23:19.557 --> 00:23:23.366
You can add 100% of the annual sum insured as the loyalty bonus.

00:23:23.366 --> 00:23:26.610
i.e. you can do it until base sum insured, you can't go above that.

00:23:26.635 --> 00:23:29.026
And you can carry it forward in the coming years.

00:23:29.051 --> 00:23:32.724
The next feature is 'restoration', which is the most interesting in my opinion...

00:23:32.724 --> 00:23:35.015
because you'll find a lot of loopholes in this condition.

00:23:35.040 --> 00:23:37.241
Let's open it on both sides.

00:23:37.241 --> 00:23:41.426
HDFC states 'Automatic Restore Benefit' and ICICI states 'Reset Benefit'.

00:23:41.451 --> 00:23:45.184
So let's look at ICICI's Evelate's reset benefit.

00:23:45.209 --> 00:23:49.387
It's written that we will reset upto 100% of the annual sum insured.

00:23:49.412 --> 00:23:52.565
Wherever you find annual sum insured in this policy,

00:23:52.590 --> 00:23:54.924
understand that they are talking about base sum insured.

00:23:54.949 --> 00:23:57.705
Because, they have written 'annual' instead of 'base'...

00:23:57.730 --> 00:23:58.911
After that they have also written,

00:23:58.911 --> 00:24:01.263
for any illness, disease or injury.

00:24:01.288 --> 00:24:03.600
Which means, related or unrelated.

00:24:03.600 --> 00:24:07.256
For all types of treatments, you will get this restoration benefit.

00:24:07.256 --> 00:24:10.462
They had a written a condition previously, which they have now removed.

00:24:10.462 --> 00:24:11.618
And it's a good thing.

00:24:11.643 --> 00:24:13.514
The condition was that If you have a related illness,

00:24:13.514 --> 00:24:16.249
and you get hospitalized for it, for the second time.

00:24:16.274 --> 00:24:19.863
That hospitalization should happen minimum 45 days later.

00:24:19.888 --> 00:24:21.970
If it doesn't happen like that, then you won't get restoration.

00:24:21.970 --> 00:24:23.860
But the condition is not the same now.

00:24:23.885 --> 00:24:25.926
Now we have to understand these points better.

00:24:25.951 --> 00:24:27.412
The entire story is here.

00:24:27.437 --> 00:24:30.709
Firstly, it's written the benefit will be triggered unlimited times.

00:24:30.734 --> 00:24:32.893
Nothing won't happen so easily. Read ahead.

00:24:32.918 --> 00:24:37.172
In the third point it's written, the annual sum insured including loyalty bonus.

00:24:37.197 --> 00:24:39.418
Inflation protector, power booster.

00:24:39.443 --> 00:24:43.792
should be insufficient as a result of previous claims paid in that policy year.

00:24:43.817 --> 00:24:45.136
There are two things mentioned in this.

00:24:45.161 --> 00:24:48.054
Firstly, claim utilization sequence has been taught to you.

00:24:48.079 --> 00:24:50.022
And secondly it's also mentioned that.

00:24:50.047 --> 00:24:52.638
If you want to claim the benefit of restoration.

00:24:52.663 --> 00:24:57.217
So all these types of covers must be insufficient for you to pay the claim.

00:24:57.242 --> 00:24:58.297
Only then will you get it.

00:24:58.322 --> 00:24:59.870
Let's understand this with an example.

00:24:59.895 --> 00:25:03.050
Assume you have a base sum insured of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:25:03.075 --> 00:25:05.527
'Annual sum insured' in their language.

00:25:05.552 --> 00:25:08.021
And you have a loyalty bonus of Rs 10 lakhs.

00:25:08.046 --> 00:25:11.945
Because, your policy completed a year, and you received a 20% loyalty bonus.

00:25:11.970 --> 00:25:15.893
And assume you don't have an inflation rider, and power booster rider.

00:25:15.918 --> 00:25:19.993
And you have a restoration benefit of Rs 50 lakhs together,

00:25:20.018 --> 00:25:22.231
which is not activated now and is on the side.

00:25:22.256 --> 00:25:24.512
And now your first claim comes as Rs 25 lakhs.

00:25:24.537 --> 00:25:27.617
It will be quite easily claimed from the base sum insured.

00:25:27.642 --> 00:25:29.217
For the next claim, in the same year,

00:25:29.242 --> 00:25:32.245
you have Rs 25 lakh in base sum insured.

00:25:32.270 --> 00:25:35.073
10 lakh rupees in no claim bonus or loyalty bonus.

00:25:35.098 --> 00:25:38.084
And restoration is left, but it's not activated.

00:25:38.109 --> 00:25:41.167
If you get hospitalized the same year for the second time...

00:25:41.192 --> 00:25:44.106
and your bill is lower than Rs 35 lakhs.

00:25:44.131 --> 00:25:45.267
So it will be very easily...

00:25:45.292 --> 00:25:48.589
it will be paid from the base sum insured and loyalty bonus.

00:25:48.614 --> 00:25:51.846
But let's say your claim comes to Rs 45 lakhs.

00:25:51.871 --> 00:25:55.096
So Rs 25 lakhs will be deducted from base sum insured.

00:25:55.121 --> 00:25:57.789
Rs 10 lakh will be deducted from loyalty bonus.

00:25:57.814 --> 00:26:02.464
And the remaining Rs 10 lakh will be deducted from the restoration benefit.

00:26:02.489 --> 00:26:05.395
So the restoration benefit of Rs 50 lakhs which is available with you.

00:26:05.420 --> 00:26:10.348
Rs 10 lakhs will be added to your base sum insured and restored.

00:26:10.373 --> 00:26:12.564
And later the claim will be deducted.

00:26:12.589 --> 00:26:16.329
This is because, it's written in the third point, your existing coverage...

00:26:16.354 --> 00:26:20.197
i.e. base sum assured, loyalty bonus or any rider.

00:26:20.222 --> 00:26:24.045
All of it was insufficient to pay your Rs 25 lakhs bill.

00:26:24.070 --> 00:26:25.764
Hence, restoration was applied.

00:26:25.789 --> 00:26:29.036
In most of the policies, instead of the sufficient word, it's written as...

00:26:29.036 --> 00:26:31.747
it's necessary that all your covers must be zero.

00:26:31.772 --> 00:26:34.099
I had explained that restoration to you before...

00:26:34.124 --> 00:26:35.623
it's useless.

00:26:35.648 --> 00:26:37.007
This is atleast usable.

00:26:37.032 --> 00:26:41.393
4. You won't get the restoration benefit in the first claim.

00:26:41.418 --> 00:26:43.540
You won't get it in the first year of your claim.

00:26:43.565 --> 00:26:46.263
In the 5th point it's written that the total amount of reset...

00:26:46.288 --> 00:26:49.537
will not exceed the annual sum insured for that policy year.

00:26:49.562 --> 00:26:54.192
If the case is that my total reset cannot be more than the annual sum insured,

00:26:54.217 --> 00:26:56.988
So how can I claim that thing unlimited times.

00:26:57.013 --> 00:27:00.277
Because it's written that it will be triggered unlimited times.

00:27:00.302 --> 00:27:04.068
Turns out, unlimited times doesn't mean unlimited restoration.

00:27:04.068 --> 00:27:05.637
Let's continue this example.

00:27:05.662 --> 00:27:07.755
Your second claim also got easily done.

00:27:07.780 --> 00:27:11.172
For the third claim, you are left with zero base sum assured.

00:27:11.197 --> 00:27:12.862
There is zero loyalty bonus left.

00:27:12.887 --> 00:27:14.962
And you are left with Rs 40 lakhs restoration.

00:27:14.987 --> 00:27:18.409
And now your third claim drops down to Rs 40 lakhs.

00:27:18.434 --> 00:27:22.210
This 40 lakhs amount will be restored in the base sum insured.

00:27:22.235 --> 00:27:23.584
And it will be paid.

00:27:23.609 --> 00:27:26.605
And similarly for this year, third claim onwards...

00:27:26.637 --> 00:27:28.685
The total cover is only Rs 40 lakhs.

00:27:28.710 --> 00:27:32.058
Now you use it for one claim or for multiple claims...

00:27:32.058 --> 00:27:34.295
or whether you use it for unlimited claims.

00:27:34.320 --> 00:27:36.921
You can use this Rs 40 lakhs the way you want to.

00:27:36.921 --> 00:27:38.815
So unlimited means...

00:27:38.840 --> 00:27:43.487
Your limited restoration which is 100% of your annual sum insured.

00:27:43.512 --> 00:27:47.963
In this case, for Rs 50 lakhs, by leaving the first claim,

00:27:47.988 --> 00:27:52.452
you can use it for the upcoming infinite unlimited claims.

00:27:52.477 --> 00:27:54.498
which becomes like a marketing gimmick.

00:27:54.523 --> 00:27:57.540
Because how many times do you get hospitalized in a year,

00:27:57.565 --> 00:28:00.148
But I am not saying that their reset benefit is not usable.

00:28:00.173 --> 00:28:01.070
It is usable.

00:28:01.095 --> 00:28:04.086
But this word unlimited is a little misleading.

00:28:04.086 --> 00:28:06.086
After that in my point six, it's written as...

00:28:06.086 --> 00:28:07.472
Day care or inpatient.

00:28:07.497 --> 00:28:09.363
You can get restoration in both types of treatments.

00:28:09.388 --> 00:28:12.345
But in the case of Ayush treatment, you need to get admitted.

00:28:12.345 --> 00:28:14.725
You won't get restoration in the day care.

00:28:14.750 --> 00:28:17.903
It's also written that unutilized reset benefit will not be carried forward,

00:28:17.928 --> 00:28:19.078
which is standard.

00:28:19.078 --> 00:28:22.142
If you are claiming outside India, even then you won't get it.

00:28:22.167 --> 00:28:25.470
Now let's see what does HDFC's automatic restore benefit states,

00:28:25.503 --> 00:28:29.854
In the event of complete or partial utilization of the base sum insured,

00:28:29.879 --> 00:28:33.309
the company shall restore sum insured upto base sum insured.

00:28:33.334 --> 00:28:36.519
Irrespective of the utilization of cumulative bonus,

00:28:36.544 --> 00:28:38.020
Plus benefit; Secure benefit.

00:28:38.045 --> 00:28:41.230
It means that claim utilization sequence will be followed.

00:28:41.255 --> 00:28:43.248
You will claim it from the base sum insured firstly.

00:28:43.273 --> 00:28:46.322
After that from the plus benefit and then from the secure benefit.

00:28:46.347 --> 00:28:49.024
And after that restore amount will be utilized.

00:28:49.049 --> 00:28:52.710
But to trigger restoration, all these types of coverage.

00:28:52.735 --> 00:28:55.364
It's not necessary to be zero or insufficient.

00:28:55.389 --> 00:28:58.773
If you've claimed even a little from the base sum insured.

00:28:58.798 --> 00:29:02.554
In the next claim, your base sum insured will become full again...

00:29:02.579 --> 00:29:04.119
because you have restoration.

00:29:04.144 --> 00:29:06.679
And you will get this restoration benefit in the base coverage,

00:29:06.704 --> 00:29:08.386
and in the protect benefit too.

00:29:08.411 --> 00:29:13.469
Protect benefit means you also get consumables cover in this HDFC policy,

00:29:13.494 --> 00:29:15.175
which is not available in ICICI.

00:29:15.200 --> 00:29:16.997
One more thing that you've to note is...

00:29:17.022 --> 00:29:20.944
Company shall restore sum insured upto base sum insured.

00:29:20.944 --> 00:29:27.377
It means that your base sum insured is equal to restoration benefit for one year.

00:29:27.402 --> 00:29:29.051
The same thing is for ICICI.

00:29:29.076 --> 00:29:30.602
It's written in Point A,

00:29:30.627 --> 00:29:34.439
restoration benefit shall be applied only once during each policy year.

00:29:34.464 --> 00:29:37.475
It will be written in Point B, restoration benefit would be triggered...

00:29:37.500 --> 00:29:40.581
only upon complete or partial utilization of base sum insured.

00:29:40.606 --> 00:29:42.559
By way of first claim admitted.

00:29:42.584 --> 00:29:47.157
And be available for subsequent claims thereafter in the policy year.

00:29:47.760 --> 00:29:51.763
Now it's important to combine these points and interpret it.

00:29:51.788 --> 00:29:52.923
Let's understand with an example.

00:29:52.948 --> 00:29:55.226
You've a base sum insured of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:29:55.251 --> 00:29:57.045
Plus benefit is of Rs 25 lakhs.

00:29:57.070 --> 00:29:58.308
Because this policy completed a year...

00:29:58.308 --> 00:30:00.661
&amp; you've received a plus benefit of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:30:00.686 --> 00:30:03.601
And you've a secure benefit of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:30:03.626 --> 00:30:08.584
And there is restoration benefit on the side, up to base sum assured, i.e. 50 lakhs.

00:30:08.609 --> 00:30:10.746
And now your first claim will be up to Rs 25 lakhs.

00:30:10.746 --> 00:30:13.392
You can easily claim it from the base sum insured.

00:30:13.392 --> 00:30:17.052
In the next claim, you'll have Rs 25 lakhs in base sum insured...

00:30:17.077 --> 00:30:20.841
Rs 25 lakhs in plus benefit and Rs 50 lakhs in secure benefit.

00:30:20.866 --> 00:30:22.968
But before claiming this second claim.

00:30:22.968 --> 00:30:27.242
your base sum insured has been restored from Rs 25 lakhs to 50 lakhs.

00:30:27.267 --> 00:30:30.812
It's written here that If your base sum insured gets partially utilized.

00:30:30.812 --> 00:30:31.882
It will top it up.

00:30:31.907 --> 00:30:34.345
Now, you think about it. If it's written in Point A.

00:30:34.370 --> 00:30:37.626
Restoration policy shall be applied only once, during each policy year.

00:30:37.651 --> 00:30:40.852
Does that mean If I claim it next time.

00:30:40.877 --> 00:30:44.045
So this remaining restoration benefit of Rs 25 lakhs...

00:30:44.070 --> 00:30:47.629
I won't get this because I've claimed it once this year.

00:30:47.654 --> 00:30:50.241
If you only listen to Point A, then you will assume it like that.

00:30:50.241 --> 00:30:52.086
But it's written in Point B, that...

00:30:52.111 --> 00:30:56.751
If it gets triggered once, then it will be available for subsequent claims...

00:30:56.776 --> 00:30:58.069
in that policy year.

00:30:58.094 --> 00:31:02.239
The restoration benefit which you receive equal to the maximum base sum insured.

00:31:02.264 --> 00:31:03.812
It is Rs 50 lakhs in our case.

00:31:03.837 --> 00:31:05.721
If you claim Rs 25 lakhs once.

00:31:05.746 --> 00:31:10.642
Then remaining Rs 25 lakhs will be beneficial for your future claims in the same policy year.

00:31:10.667 --> 00:31:13.357
So what does Point A mean, that you will only get it for a year.

00:31:13.382 --> 00:31:17.832
The total restoration benefit, i.e. Rs 50 lakhs.

00:31:17.857 --> 00:31:19.421
You will get that once a year.

00:31:19.446 --> 00:31:21.621
Rs 50 lakhs won't be restored either.

00:31:21.646 --> 00:31:26.128
It means this feature is providing similar type of restoration.

00:31:26.153 --> 00:31:29.625
The total restoration that you will get in both policies, in one year.

00:31:29.650 --> 00:31:32.246
It cannot be more than your base sum insured.

00:31:32.271 --> 00:31:35.496
In both the policies, second claim onwards.

00:31:35.496 --> 00:31:37.300
You can take the restoration benefit.

00:31:37.325 --> 00:31:42.935
And the total restoration in both policies, you can utilize them in multiple claims.

00:31:42.960 --> 00:31:45.510
But If you only look at the promotional material,

00:31:45.535 --> 00:31:48.314
then you will realize you only get one restoration benefit in HDFC.

00:31:48.339 --> 00:31:50.365
And you get unlimited time in ICICI.

00:31:51.144 --> 00:31:55.520
And fun fact, If you truly need unlimited restoration in HDFC,

00:31:55.545 --> 00:31:57.770
So it has a 70 or 80 rider.

00:31:57.795 --> 00:32:01.483
If you add that, then you will get truly unlimited restoration.

00:32:01.508 --> 00:32:04.225
It means after Rs 50 lakhs entirely.

00:32:04.225 --> 00:32:06.620
You can get an additional restoration of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:32:06.645 --> 00:32:10.203
The next feature is 'Domiciliary Hospitalization'.

00:32:10.228 --> 00:32:13.812
There are certain exclusions in ICICI. From A to K.

00:32:13.836 --> 00:32:16.756
Hence, If you have a requirement of hospitalization at home,

00:32:16.781 --> 00:32:19.077
then whether the company will pay for it's expenses?

00:32:19.102 --> 00:32:21.966
In ICICI's case, company will provide it.

00:32:21.991 --> 00:32:25.239
But you must have hospitalization of minimum three days.

00:32:25.264 --> 00:32:28.918
You must have a written advice of a medical practitioner.

00:32:29.299 --> 00:32:30.617
And even after that,

00:32:30.642 --> 00:32:34.578
you won't get cover for diseases listed from A to K.

00:32:34.603 --> 00:32:36.231
Whereas it's written in HDFC that,

00:32:36.256 --> 00:32:40.195
you must get it in writing from the medical practitioner, similar to ICICI.

00:32:40.220 --> 00:32:44.642
The patient's condition must be that he should not be able to move...

00:32:44.667 --> 00:32:47.509
Or not being able to take to the hospital, they will get it then.

00:32:47.534 --> 00:32:51.057
Or else he is admitted at home, because he didn't get a room in the hospital.

00:32:51.082 --> 00:32:54.009
Now this doesn't mean that ICICI is not good and HDFC is better.

00:32:54.034 --> 00:32:57.149
This means that ICICI's plan is quite affordable.

00:32:57.174 --> 00:32:59.944
And If we consider all the terms and conditions,

00:32:59.969 --> 00:33:02.313
then we are buying this plan with our eyes open.

00:33:02.338 --> 00:33:04.748
This comparison is done to empower you.

00:33:04.748 --> 00:33:08.733
If you keep your premiums low and opt for a policy that has a useful feature,

00:33:08.758 --> 00:33:10.370
then our objective is fulfilled.

00:33:10.399 --> 00:33:11.979
ZONE BASED POLICIES

00:33:12.004 --> 00:33:15.647
One more thing you need to remember is, ICICI's policy is zone based policy.

00:33:15.672 --> 00:33:19.160
It means If you take it in metro cities, then it's premium will be higher.

00:33:19.185 --> 00:33:20.948
because the treatment cost is higher as well.

00:33:20.973 --> 00:33:24.214
And If you purchase it in tier 3 city, then it's cost will be lower.

00:33:24.365 --> 00:33:26.342
So it's divided into zones A, B, C and D.

00:33:26.367 --> 00:33:29.551
You are punished based on zone based policy, in certain policies.

00:33:29.576 --> 00:33:33.404
It means that maybe you added your native's address, but you live in a city...

00:33:33.429 --> 00:33:35.402
If you visit to take treatment in a city.

00:33:35.427 --> 00:33:38.721
In this case, the company can suggest opting for the treatment at your native,

00:33:38.746 --> 00:33:40.338
for you to get a 100% claim.

00:33:40.338 --> 00:33:42.392
But If you opt for it in the city, then 20% copay will be levied.

00:33:42.417 --> 00:33:44.642
Thankfully there is no punishment in ICICI.

00:33:44.667 --> 00:33:46.435
However, there is definitely a condition,

00:33:46.460 --> 00:33:49.885
that your address must be accurate at all times.

00:33:49.910 --> 00:33:51.863
If you have changed the address,

00:33:51.888 --> 00:33:54.776
that changed address must be updated in the policy.

00:33:54.776 --> 00:33:57.026
Or else your claim will get rejected.

00:33:57.051 --> 00:34:01.633
As long as your address is accurate, whether you get treated in tier 1 or 2.

00:34:01.658 --> 00:34:02.879
There is no problem with it.

00:34:02.904 --> 00:34:06.552
The next feature is consumables, which is under the name 'Protect benefits' in HDFC.

00:34:06.577 --> 00:34:10.408
Consumables means gloves, PPE kit, and other expenses.

00:34:10.433 --> 00:34:12.570
After the treatment, which are not usually covered.

00:34:12.595 --> 00:34:14.569
You will also get that covered in the HDFC plan.

00:34:14.594 --> 00:34:17.733
But in ICICI's case, you won't get that cover inbuilt,

00:34:17.758 --> 00:34:19.587
you'll have to get a separate rider.

00:34:19.612 --> 00:34:21.612
There is another feature as annual health check up.

00:34:21.637 --> 00:34:24.616
You get that in HDFC, but not in ICICI.

00:34:24.641 --> 00:34:26.856
You will have to get a separate rider for that.

00:34:26.881 --> 00:34:30.677
You can compare all these features easily.

00:34:30.702 --> 00:34:32.680
And you have policy bazaar's link in the description.

00:34:32.705 --> 00:34:34.957
RIDERS, ARE THEY USEFUL?

00:34:34.982 --> 00:34:38.491
Now since we are talking about riders, then we have to see that...

00:34:38.516 --> 00:34:43.530
If ICICI is affordable, and you have to add a lot of riders to it, to make it usable.

00:34:43.555 --> 00:34:46.867
So which are those riders, which combined together makes a useable plan.

00:34:46.892 --> 00:34:49.322
I kept both the plans side by side.

00:34:49.347 --> 00:34:51.753
HDFC's base cover is kept at Rs 25 lakhs...

00:34:51.778 --> 00:34:53.748
and the base cover in ICICI is Rs 50 lakhs.

00:34:53.748 --> 00:34:54.857
This is because...

00:34:54.882 --> 00:34:56.772
In HDFC, along with the base cover of Rs 25 lakhs,

00:34:56.797 --> 00:34:58.812
you get Rs 25 lakhs extra from Day 1,

00:34:58.837 --> 00:35:00.280
in the form of secure benefit.

00:35:00.305 --> 00:35:02.458
It doesn't have a lot of hidden conditions.

00:35:02.483 --> 00:35:04.480
This is not a fair comparison by the way.

00:35:04.480 --> 00:35:07.129
If we keep HDFCs base sum insured as Rs 25 lakhs.

00:35:07.154 --> 00:35:10.657
Then their cover will become triple, i.e. Rs 75 lakhs, in the third year.

00:35:10.682 --> 00:35:13.572
Whereas, ICICI's 25 lakhs base sum insured,

00:35:13.597 --> 00:35:16.354
will double in the fifth year to 1 Crore.

00:35:16.379 --> 00:35:17.711
Just something to keep in mind.

00:35:17.736 --> 00:35:19.277
Even then HDFC is quite expensive.

00:35:19.302 --> 00:35:22.964
Now the premium is Rs 19,300 and Rs 12, 882.

00:35:22.989 --> 00:35:26.398
I have added a rider in HDFC, in the name of 'unlimited restore'.

00:35:26.423 --> 00:35:29.168
Because, in their policy, I will get the restoration only once a year.

00:35:29.193 --> 00:35:31.910
But If you want that you get unlimited restoration,

00:35:31.935 --> 00:35:34.222
then you add a very affordable premium.

00:35:34.247 --> 00:35:36.788
Hence, I have not added another rider in HDFC.

00:35:36.813 --> 00:35:38.838
But in ICICI, there are a lot of riders.

00:35:38.863 --> 00:35:40.671
1. Infinite Care.

00:35:40.696 --> 00:35:46.139
It means, in one single claim, you can claim for an infinite amount.

00:35:46.164 --> 00:35:48.586
In your entire lifetime, instead of once a year.

00:35:48.611 --> 00:35:49.937
Once the entire year.

00:35:49.962 --> 00:35:53.131
It means it's usable for the most serious illnesses.

00:35:53.156 --> 00:35:57.811
The rider is formed keeping in mind that very few people will claim it.

00:35:57.836 --> 00:35:59.249
So it could be possible that,

00:35:59.274 --> 00:36:03.137
you keep paying Rs 189/ year as loading as the premium keeps increasing on it.

00:36:03.162 --> 00:36:05.120
But you won't be able to claim this benefit.

00:36:05.145 --> 00:36:07.362
And if you are highly paranoid like me,

00:36:07.387 --> 00:36:10.230
even then opt for the terms and conditions before purchasing it.

00:36:10.255 --> 00:36:12.773
It has a total of nine terms and conditions.

00:36:12.798 --> 00:36:16.312
It is written quite nicely that without any limits on the annual sum insured,

00:36:16.312 --> 00:36:18.565
you will be given to claim once in your lifetime.

00:36:18.590 --> 00:36:23.014
Apart from Ayush Day Care treatments, you will get the cover in other types.

00:36:23.039 --> 00:36:25.286
If you don't take the other while purchasing the policy,

00:36:25.286 --> 00:36:27.305
you can take it in the next two years.

00:36:27.334 --> 00:36:28.354
You won't get it after that.

00:36:28.379 --> 00:36:30.000
If you opt for it once, then...

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:34.531
you won't be able to opt out until you claim once in your policy lifetime.

00:36:34.556 --> 00:36:37.581
5. Total sum assured, i.e. Annual sum insured.

00:36:37.606 --> 00:36:39.345
Loyalty bonus, If accrued.

00:36:39.370 --> 00:36:41.460
Power booster if opted and approved.

00:36:41.485 --> 00:36:45.041
Inflation protector shall be utilized as per the following sequence.

00:36:45.066 --> 00:36:47.044
It means firstly annual sum insured will be considered.

00:36:47.069 --> 00:36:48.542
After that, loyalty bonus will be considered.

00:36:48.567 --> 00:36:51.088
After that power booster and then inflation protector.

00:36:51.113 --> 00:36:55.043
After that your inflinite claim will be applicable.

00:36:55.068 --> 00:36:56.243
In the next point,  it's written...

00:36:56.268 --> 00:36:59.229
after utilization of all the above-mentioned sum insured.

00:36:59.254 --> 00:37:02.693
The total sum insured shall be reduced to zero.

00:37:02.718 --> 00:37:06.323
It means that your last coverage which is the inflation protector.

00:37:06.348 --> 00:37:08.944
If 1-2 lakh remains.

00:37:08.969 --> 00:37:13.153
And you get admitted in a hospital and the time of infinite claim occurs.

00:37:13.178 --> 00:37:15.193
Because the medical bill has become huge,

00:37:15.218 --> 00:37:16.909
then you won't be able to claim.

00:37:16.934 --> 00:37:19.937
Because little money remained in the inflation protector.

00:37:19.962 --> 00:37:23.655
Firstly, use it, make it zero, and once you go to the next claim.

00:37:23.680 --> 00:37:24.790
Only then will you get infinite.

00:37:24.815 --> 00:37:27.859
Next point is If you take voluntary co-payment.

00:37:27.884 --> 00:37:31.145
then a copayment will also be levied on this infinite cover.

00:37:31.145 --> 00:37:33.316
Don't do this, that you've taken the co-payment as well.

00:37:33.341 --> 00:37:35.214
And If you have also taken an infinite rider.

00:37:35.239 --> 00:37:38.035
There are certain other aspects wherein you can't take claim.

00:37:38.060 --> 00:37:41.085
And lastly it's written that your room category will also be applied.

00:37:41.110 --> 00:37:43.906
So if you are taking the rider, then you should not opt for co-pay.

00:37:43.931 --> 00:37:46.635
You must opt for modifying room rent rider,

00:37:46.635 --> 00:37:48.697
so that your room rent limit gets removed.

00:37:48.722 --> 00:37:53.081
Otherwise this will become an infinite percentage bill of an infinite claim,

00:37:53.106 --> 00:37:54.717
and you will have to incur it.

00:37:54.742 --> 00:37:56.616
And the point number six states that,

00:37:56.616 --> 00:37:59.890
If I want to turn these four types of covers into zero,

00:37:59.915 --> 00:38:04.427
then for one particular case this infinite cover will be denied.

00:38:04.452 --> 00:38:06.239
So in my opinion, I must skip this rider,

00:38:06.264 --> 00:38:09.510
you must learn how to increase your base sum insured.

00:38:09.535 --> 00:38:12.389
If you are taking adequate base cover, then you are sorted.

00:38:12.414 --> 00:38:15.843
Because at the same time, you are also getting a renewal bonus in both policies.

00:38:15.868 --> 00:38:18.164
So after some years, your cover will get doubled anyway.

00:38:18.189 --> 00:38:21.317
If you are opting for HDFC, then your cover will be tripled.

00:38:21.342 --> 00:38:23.511
The next rider in ICICI is power booster.

00:38:23.536 --> 00:38:27.427
Power booster means you will get 100% sum insured every year,

00:38:27.452 --> 00:38:28.365
regardless of claims.

00:38:28.390 --> 00:38:29.684
This is quite amazing.

00:38:29.709 --> 00:38:32.484
i.e. This policy is for Rs 50 lakhs, and will become Rs 1 Crore next year.

00:38:32.484 --> 00:38:34.111
After that it will be 1.5 Crore.

00:38:34.136 --> 00:38:36.699
In the next 10 years, it will become Rs 5 Crore 50 lakhs.

00:38:36.724 --> 00:38:39.647
There is no upper limit. You can keep adding unlimited.

00:38:39.647 --> 00:38:42.428
Technically you are buying an infinite cover policy.

00:38:42.453 --> 00:38:46.478
There are no hidden terms and conditions in power booster, which is a good thing.

00:38:46.503 --> 00:38:48.189
But in point number 3, it's written...

00:38:48.189 --> 00:38:52.491
In case the insured person opts out of this cover at any time of the renewal.

00:38:52.516 --> 00:38:56.360
All the bonus accumulated under power booster will be reduced to zero.

00:38:56.385 --> 00:38:59.608
Now you will say why should I opt out of this amazing rider.

00:38:59.633 --> 00:39:02.521
It will become a 10 crore policy after 20 years.

00:39:02.546 --> 00:39:05.520
And 20 crore policy after 40 years.

00:39:05.545 --> 00:39:07.252
You will opt out because...

00:39:07.277 --> 00:39:10.190
because this plan is cheaper today, it won't be tomorrow.

00:39:10.215 --> 00:39:12.000
Premiums of health insurance keeps increasing with age.

00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:13.407
They are not fixed like term insurance.

00:39:13.432 --> 00:39:17.243
Your total premium could increase so much in the future, you will think that...

00:39:17.268 --> 00:39:19.008
You must remove this rider.

00:39:19.033 --> 00:39:22.800
If you remove it, then the added sum insured will be removed.

00:39:22.825 --> 00:39:25.151
After that the next rider is jump start.

00:39:25.176 --> 00:39:28.687
In jump start, it states that the waiting period in your pre existing diseases.

00:39:28.712 --> 00:39:31.947
Usually of 3 years, you can make it up 30 days.

00:39:31.972 --> 00:39:36.190
That is you can treat pre existing disease from the 31st day.

00:39:36.215 --> 00:39:39.591
The rider's price is the most expensive in this case, which is Rs 3,800.

00:39:39.616 --> 00:39:43.101
You must only consider when you have any pre existing diseases.

00:39:43.126 --> 00:39:45.291
If you are plannig a surgery or a treatment.

00:39:45.316 --> 00:39:47.605
But not without knowing the terms and conditions.

00:39:47.630 --> 00:39:52.107
And as you can see, one of the longest list of terms and conditions is of jumpstart.

00:39:52.132 --> 00:39:54.466
So it's written the diseases that you declare.

00:39:54.491 --> 00:39:57.953
and the diseases that we (the company) accepts, that will be covered.

00:39:57.978 --> 00:40:01.151
This cover will be available only during inception of the policy...

00:40:01.151 --> 00:40:03.371
or upon addition of a new member.

00:40:03.396 --> 00:40:06.114
Once chosen, this optional cover will have to be opted for...

00:40:06.139 --> 00:40:08.657
a period of three continuous policy years.

00:40:08.682 --> 00:40:12.042
What will happen after three years, this rider will be removed from the policy.

00:40:12.067 --> 00:40:13.736
But it's not written that,

00:40:13.736 --> 00:40:16.607
your normal premium will increase after three years.

00:40:16.635 --> 00:40:18.157
Your money won't be saved.

00:40:18.182 --> 00:40:19.856
You might think that you need to pay upto three years.

00:40:19.881 --> 00:40:22.257
After that premium will reduce. No, it won't happen like that.

00:40:22.282 --> 00:40:24.106
There is a term as loading.

00:40:24.106 --> 00:40:26.772
Loading states by looking at your pre-existing conditions,

00:40:26.772 --> 00:40:28.254
your premium is increased.

00:40:28.279 --> 00:40:30.234
Assume that and it will happen with you.

00:40:30.259 --> 00:40:32.918
Don't presume that your premium will decrease after three years.

00:40:32.943 --> 00:40:34.877
After that it's written list of diseases covered.

00:40:34.877 --> 00:40:39.075
Asthma, diabetes, Hypertension i.e. high BP, Hyperlipidemia i.e. high cholesterol.

00:40:39.100 --> 00:40:41.102
Obesity, coronary artery disease.

00:40:41.127 --> 00:40:44.540
These six diseases have been further explained.

00:40:44.565 --> 00:40:47.202
What are these? and when will you get a cover on it?

00:40:47.227 --> 00:40:51.228
For eg: Coronary artery disease, PTCA done prior to one year.

00:40:51.253 --> 00:40:55.920
PTCA means coronary angioplasty, i.e. the procedure to insert a stent in the artery.

00:40:55.945 --> 00:40:57.375
Further it's also written that,

00:40:57.400 --> 00:41:00.656
Angioplasty with or without stenting for treatment of narrowing or blockage...

00:41:00.681 --> 00:41:04.597
of a minimum of 50% of one or more major coronary arteries.

00:41:04.597 --> 00:41:08.437
It's not that you have a blockage and it's appeared in the test.

00:41:08.462 --> 00:41:11.677
There is a coronary CT angiography, in which you have to...

00:41:11.702 --> 00:41:15.641
It's a non-invasive test, a CT scan is conducted to show the blockage.

00:41:15.666 --> 00:41:18.946
and when you get to know about it, then it's not considered a pre existing disease.

00:41:18.971 --> 00:41:21.798
As far as this policy or jumpstart rider is confirmed...

00:41:21.823 --> 00:41:23.818
Your operation is confirmed and should be done..

00:41:23.843 --> 00:41:26.010
More than one stent should be added.

00:41:26.010 --> 00:41:28.718
There must be 50% blockage, only then will you be able to cover it.

00:41:28.743 --> 00:41:30.029
This is the claim protector.

00:41:30.054 --> 00:41:32.810
This is the consumables cover, i.e. gloves, PPE kit, etc.

00:41:32.835 --> 00:41:34.741
All the out of pocket expenses.

00:41:34.766 --> 00:41:36.860
You will have to take an additional rider to cover that.

00:41:36.885 --> 00:41:38.323
Amounting to Rs 652.

00:41:38.348 --> 00:41:40.422
The next rider is of pre-existing disease.

00:41:40.447 --> 00:41:43.703
If you want instead of three, you only have two years of waiting period.

00:41:43.728 --> 00:41:47.174
Or it should only be for a year, then you can pay the premium immediately.

00:41:47.199 --> 00:41:50.170
You also need to think If you need the cover immediately.

00:41:50.195 --> 00:41:52.092
Or If you don't want to wait for three years,

00:41:52.117 --> 00:41:53.292
then you will have to add.

00:41:53.317 --> 00:41:56.319
The next rider is inflation protect, which we have repeatedly come across.

00:41:56.344 --> 00:41:57.870
It's also known as sum insured.

00:41:57.870 --> 00:41:58.631
It's for Rs 150.

00:41:58.656 --> 00:42:00.761
It states that as per the previous year's inflation rate,

00:42:00.786 --> 00:42:02.201
your base sum assured will be increased.

00:42:02.226 --> 00:42:03.793
Since this rider is very cheap.

00:42:03.818 --> 00:42:05.480
So it's not bad to opt for this.

00:42:05.507 --> 00:42:07.934
After that is room modifier, which you have to purchase.

00:42:07.959 --> 00:42:10.777
Now you need to opt for select and click on 'any room'.

00:42:10.802 --> 00:42:11.765
And you will have to add this.

00:42:11.790 --> 00:42:13.646
The next rider is annual health check up.

00:42:13.671 --> 00:42:16.220
It's included in HDFC, in the base plan.

00:42:16.245 --> 00:42:18.350
You have to take it separately in ICICI.

00:42:18.375 --> 00:42:22.068
Maybe all types of tests might not be covered in this.

00:42:22.093 --> 00:42:23.951
Next is 'BeFit C'.

00:42:23.976 --> 00:42:28.116
This BeFit C states that upto four out patient consultations...

00:42:28.157 --> 00:42:29.679
i.e. you'll get doctor consultations,

00:42:29.704 --> 00:42:33.205
routine diagnostic and minor procedure cover of Rs 1000.

00:42:33.230 --> 00:42:36.427
Pharmacy 1000, six sections of physiotherapy, e counselling,

00:42:36.427 --> 00:42:39.260
diet and nutrition, e consultation each.

00:42:39.285 --> 00:42:42.294
This is something to create a package and then form a rider.

00:42:42.319 --> 00:42:43.621
I won't opt for it.

00:42:43.646 --> 00:42:47.037
And in HDFC, you will get an OPD cover in built.

00:42:47.062 --> 00:42:48.587
There is a separate render in this.

00:42:48.612 --> 00:42:51.121
And this physiotherapy, e counselling, etc.

00:42:51.146 --> 00:42:52.980
Most people don't use this.

00:42:53.005 --> 00:42:54.444
It's ok even If you don't take it.

00:42:54.469 --> 00:42:56.715
But you only have to manage the OPD expense.

00:42:56.740 --> 00:42:59.956
The next is 'specific disease waiting period' which is of 2 years, I told you.

00:43:00.402 --> 00:43:03.999
You can give a premium and change it from 2 to 1 year.

00:43:04.024 --> 00:43:06.171
I think the premium is too high...

00:43:06.196 --> 00:43:10.112
and it's not like jumpstart that it's waiting period could go reach 30 days.

00:43:10.137 --> 00:43:11.192
It will only be for a year.

00:43:11.217 --> 00:43:13.736
So as per me, this must not be added.

00:43:13.761 --> 00:43:16.890
After that, dependent accomodation, durable medical cover,

00:43:16.915 --> 00:43:20.258
After that, there are two riders which I haven't seen... you can read them.

00:43:20.283 --> 00:43:22.918
If I add a rider in ICICI.

00:43:22.943 --> 00:43:26.482
So I will do the room modifier thing because it must be done.

00:43:26.507 --> 00:43:28.966
I could also make inflation, because it's only for Rs 150.

00:43:28.991 --> 00:43:30.961
And if because of inflation, my cover keeps increasing...

00:43:30.986 --> 00:43:32.472
then there is no major issue.

00:43:32.505 --> 00:43:34.751
However, it won't increase due to medical inflation.

00:43:34.776 --> 00:43:36.302
It will increase because of CPI inflation.

00:43:36.327 --> 00:43:39.164
I can also take claim protector and If you want to get it equal to HDFC.

00:43:39.189 --> 00:43:40.856
I can also take claim protector.

00:43:40.881 --> 00:43:42.383
Because this is consumables cover.

00:43:42.408 --> 00:43:44.552
And as I told you about power booster.

00:43:44.577 --> 00:43:48.166
There are no hidden terms and conditions in terms of usability.

00:43:48.191 --> 00:43:50.038
But If we opted out in the future,

00:43:50.063 --> 00:43:54.091
then all the added power booster will disappear.

00:43:54.116 --> 00:43:57.937
And for this, I believe the premium will become so unaffordable...

00:43:57.962 --> 00:44:00.424
and I might have to leave it and it will be removed.

00:44:00.449 --> 00:44:03.690
I won't add it today. I want to keep my premium slow.

00:44:03.715 --> 00:44:07.350
By doing this, my premium in ICICI comes to Rs 14,315.

00:44:07.375 --> 00:44:10.086
Whereas, in HDFC, it comes to Rs 19,300.

00:44:10.111 --> 00:44:13.105
In ICICI, the premium is less, but there are some key differences.

00:44:13.130 --> 00:44:15.139
In HDFC, you get base sum assured...

00:44:15.164 --> 00:44:17.466
and you also get a secured benefit along with that.

00:44:17.491 --> 00:44:21.732
and you will also get 50% plus benefit, which is also called as no claim bonus.

00:44:21.757 --> 00:44:23.004
Irrespective of claims.

00:44:23.029 --> 00:44:25.757
It means my total cover will triple in the third year.

00:44:25.782 --> 00:44:28.608
If you look at it that way, then the premium will be justified.

00:44:28.633 --> 00:44:30.011
Whereas in ICICI,

00:44:30.036 --> 00:44:34.135
you won't get any secured benefit, you will only get the base sum assured.

00:44:34.160 --> 00:44:37.871
After that you will get a no-claim bonus, which is 20% instead of 50%.

00:44:37.896 --> 00:44:40.017
i.e. your cover will double in the fifth year.

00:44:40.042 --> 00:44:42.376
Whereas, in HDFC, the cover triples in the third year.

00:44:42.401 --> 00:44:46.015
You also get maternity cover in ICICI and it must've been added in HDFC too.

00:44:46.040 --> 00:44:47.899
But the terms for both are not good.

00:44:47.924 --> 00:44:51.059
If the annual premium you give and the waiting period.

00:44:51.084 --> 00:44:55.698
It turns out you will pay your entire delivery expense in premiums and get it back.

00:44:55.723 --> 00:44:57.422
So calculate that once.

00:44:57.447 --> 00:45:00.560
You also get a bariatric surgery in ICICI.

00:45:00.585 --> 00:45:03.398
But understand this fancy name once.

00:45:03.423 --> 00:45:07.061
Bariatric surgery is done on highly obese people, by cutting their organs.

00:45:07.086 --> 00:45:10.228
Their weight loss surgery is done, so that they survive in the future.

00:45:10.253 --> 00:45:14.227
So If you don't come in the category, then there is no requirement for you.

00:45:14.252 --> 00:45:15.276
The conclusion is...

00:45:15.301 --> 00:45:17.930
If now you've understood when do you get claims in ICICI plan.

00:45:17.955 --> 00:45:19.876
When do you get it, when you don't.

00:45:19.901 --> 00:45:21.957
And which features are helpful for you.

00:45:21.982 --> 00:45:26.009
You can take it with open eyes, and you can save the premium too.

00:45:26.034 --> 00:45:29.051
So If you want more cover in a lower premium.

00:45:29.083 --> 00:45:31.710
If you also need jumpstart rider for pre existing diseases,

00:45:31.735 --> 00:45:33.650
then you can consider ICICI for it.

00:45:33.675 --> 00:45:37.088
But If you need a no compromise policy with triple coverage.

00:45:37.113 --> 00:45:39.535
And simple to understand terms and conditions.

00:45:39.560 --> 00:45:42.028
Then you can opt for HDFC with high premium.

00:45:42.053 --> 00:45:44.767
HOW TO LOWER THE PREMIUM?

00:45:44.792 --> 00:45:47.597
Now how can premiums be lowered further from here,

00:45:47.622 --> 00:45:48.678
you've two tricks on that too.

00:45:48.703 --> 00:45:51.663
You have an option in HDFC of 'aggregate deductible'.

00:45:51.688 --> 00:45:55.307
You can choose an aggregate deductible amount as per your wish.

00:45:55.332 --> 00:45:57.382
For example, you chose Rs 50,000.

00:45:57.407 --> 00:46:00.996
It means the bill formed in a year.

00:46:00.996 --> 00:46:03.508
in one claim or in multiple claims.

00:46:03.533 --> 00:46:07.138
You've to provide first Rs 50,000 of that medical bill.

00:46:07.163 --> 00:46:09.317
Not per hospitalization, but per year.

00:46:09.342 --> 00:46:11.495
It doesn't mean that you visited the hospital 10 times a year,

00:46:11.495 --> 00:46:13.000
then you'll have to provide Rs 5 lakhs for it.

00:46:13.025 --> 00:46:14.822
You only have to provide Rs 50,000.

00:46:14.847 --> 00:46:17.917
You can claim the remaining from HDFC.

00:46:17.942 --> 00:46:20.031
If you chose this deductible,

00:46:20.056 --> 00:46:22.637
which is actually not a bad deal compared to co-pay.

00:46:22.662 --> 00:46:25.236
In which, 20% of the admissable claim amount is levied.

00:46:25.261 --> 00:46:28.587
You'll have to provide 20%, if you receive a Rs 50 lakh claim.

00:46:28.612 --> 00:46:31.018
Here your upside is capped on Rs 50,000.

00:46:31.043 --> 00:46:34.441
By choosing this, your premium drastically reduces.

00:46:34.466 --> 00:46:35.897
And If you notice here.

00:46:35.922 --> 00:46:39.359
Then the premium discount you receive on the deductible of Rs 50,000.

00:46:39.384 --> 00:46:41.768
You won't get the double discount on Rs 1 lakh.

00:46:41.816 --> 00:46:45.495
It really doesn't make sense that you choose the deductible of Rs 1 lakh.

00:46:45.520 --> 00:46:48.402
Mathematically speaking, you have a higher benefit on Rs 50,000.

00:46:48.427 --> 00:46:49.670
You choose this at the time,

00:46:49.670 --> 00:46:54.198
when you decide not to claim in the next 10 years, and you save Rs 50,000.

00:46:54.223 --> 00:46:56.074
Before paying it for the first time.

00:46:56.099 --> 00:47:00.142
Or else you have a policy, i.e. a different policy.

00:47:00.288 --> 00:47:02.118
And the first claim could be fulfilled from there too.

00:47:02.143 --> 00:47:04.623
SUPER TOP UP

00:47:04.648 --> 00:47:09.303
2. Taking a huge cover while keeping the premium lower is a super top-up policy.

00:47:09.328 --> 00:47:12.116
And this comes at an affforable rate than the normal health insurance policy.

00:47:12.141 --> 00:47:15.920
And it's affordable because the first 5 or 10 lakhs,

00:47:15.945 --> 00:47:18.097
Any deductible limit that you choose.

00:47:18.122 --> 00:47:20.926
You will get a claim higher than that.

00:47:20.951 --> 00:47:23.475
For eg: You got a super top-up policy of Rs 50 lakhs.

00:47:23.500 --> 00:47:25.577
Aggregate deductible is of Rs 10 lakhs.

00:47:25.602 --> 00:47:26.832
So it means that year,

00:47:26.857 --> 00:47:29.159
you will have to accumulate the first Rs 10 lakhs from somewhere else.

00:47:29.184 --> 00:47:32.870
And if your claim is more than 10 lakhs, then any claims in excess of that.

00:47:32.895 --> 00:47:34.657
You will get that from super top up.

00:47:34.682 --> 00:47:37.557
The trick is whichever deductible you choose.

00:47:37.582 --> 00:47:39.822
The insurance from there until now.

00:47:39.847 --> 00:47:41.720
It should be sorted with the main policy.

00:47:41.745 --> 00:47:45.146
And the insurance above that must be sorted with your super top up.

00:47:45.171 --> 00:47:47.659
There is a top up policy, which you have to simply ignore.

00:47:47.684 --> 00:47:49.183
You must take a super top up.

00:47:49.208 --> 00:47:53.305
Because, you only get one hit to claim the deductible in top up.

00:47:53.330 --> 00:47:55.452
Whereas, the deductible in super top,

00:47:55.477 --> 00:47:58.568
it will still be counted even after hitting multiple claims.

00:47:58.593 --> 00:48:00.934
So the practical usage of super top up increases,

00:48:00.934 --> 00:48:03.895
and it could happen that you might not get claim in the case of top up.

00:48:03.920 --> 00:48:06.513
